EXPERIMENT – 1
Basic Collection Creation & Dropping – LMS)
🔹 Aim
To create and drop a collection without constraints.
🔹 Queries (Paste in MongoDB Compass → Shell)
use lms
db.createCollection("courses")
🔹 O/P
{ ok: 1 }
show collections
🔹 O/P
courses
db.courses.drop()
🔹 O/P
true
🔹 Result
The collection courses was successfully created and verified. After executing the drop command, it was removed from the database.


EXPERIMENT – 2
(Collection with Required Fields & Data Types)
🔹 Aim

To enforce required fields using schema validation.

🔹 Query
db.createCollection("courses", {
  validator: {
    $jsonSchema: {
      bsonType: "object",
      required: ["courseName", "instructor", "duration"],
      properties: {
        courseName: { bsonType: "string" },
        instructor: { bsonType: "string" },
        duration: { bsonType: "int" },
        active: { bsonType: "bool" }
      }
    }
  }
}) 
Valid Insert
db.courses.insertOne({
  courseName: "DBMS",
  instructor: "Dr. Kumar",
  duration: 45,
  active: true
})
🔹 O/P
{ acknowledged: true, insertedId: ObjectId("...") }
🔹 Invalid Insert (Missing required field)
db.courses.insertOne({
  courseName: "OS",
  duration: 40
})
🔹 O/P
MongoServerError: Document failed validation
🔹 Result
The collection enforces required fields. Valid documents are inserted, while invalid ones are rejected.

EXPERIMENT – 3
(Advanced Validation – Enum, Range, Pattern)
🔹 Aim

To apply advanced validation rules.

🔹 Query
db.createCollection("students", {
  validator: {
    $jsonSchema: {
      bsonType: "object",
      required: ["studentId", "name", "course", "grade"],
      properties: {
        studentId: {
          bsonType: "string",
          pattern: "^STU[0-9]{3}$"
        },
        name: {
          bsonType: "string",
          minLength: 3
        },
        course: {
          enum: ["DBMS", "OS", "CN", "AI"]
        },
        grade: {
          bsonType: "double",
          minimum: 0,
          maximum: 10
        }
      }
    }
  },
  validationLevel: "strict",
  validationAction: "error"
})
🔹 Valid Insert
db.students.insertOne({
  studentId: "STU101",
  name: "Rahul",
  course: "DBMS",
  grade: 8.5
})
🔹 O/P
{ acknowledged: true, insertedId: ObjectId("...") }
🔹 Invalid Insert
db.students.insertOne({
  studentId: "101",
  name: "A",
  course: "Math",
  grade: 15
})
🔹 O/P
MongoServerError: Document failed validation
🔹 Result

Advanced validation ensures only properly formatted student data is inserted.

EXPERIMENT – 4
(Modify Validation on Existing Collection)
🔹 Aim

To add validation rules to an existing collection.

🔹 Queries
db.createCollection("instructors")
db.runCommand({
  collMod: "instructors",
  validator: {
    $jsonSchema: {
      bsonType: "object",
      required: ["instructorId", "name", "salary"],
      properties: {
        instructorId: {
          bsonType: "string",
          pattern: "^INS[0-9]{3}$"
        },
        name: {
          bsonType: "string",
          minLength: 3
        },
        salary: {
          bsonType: "double",
          minimum: 20000
        }
      }
    }
  },
  validationLevel: "moderate"
})
🔹 O/P
{ ok: 1 }
🔹 Result
Validation rules were successfully added to an existing collection using collMod.

